%N A328122 Number of rooted level-1 phylogenetic networks with n labeled leaves.
%H A328122 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A328122/b328122.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..335</a>
%H A328122 Lily Agranat-Tamir, Michael Fuchs, Bernhard Gittenberger, Noah A. Rosenberg, Karthik V. Seetharaman, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aam.2026.103131">Combinatorial comparison of general galled trees, time-consistent galled trees, and simplex time-consistent galled trees</a>, Adv. Appl. Math. 180, 103131 (2026). See Table 2.
%H A328122 François Bienvenu, Jean-Jil Duchamps, Michael Fuchs, and Tsan-Cheng Yu, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.19454">The B_2 index of galled trees</a>, arXiv:2407.19454 [q-bio.PE], 2024. See p. 5.
%H A328122 Mathilde Bouvel, Philippe Gambette and Marefatollah Mansouri, <a href="http://user.math.uzh.ch/bouvel/publications/BouvelGambetteMansouri.mw">Maple worksheet</a>
%H A328122 Mathilde Bouvel, Philippe Gambette and Marefatollah Mansouri, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1909.10460">Counting Phylogenetic Networks of level 1 and 2</a>, arXiv:1909.10460 [math.CO], 2019.
%F A328122 Bouvel, Gambette and Mansouri provide (among other results) a closed formula for a(n), an equation and a closed form for the associated exponential generating function, and an asymptotic estimate of a(n). See their Section 5.
%F A328122 E.g.f. satisfies A(x) = x + (1/2)*A(x)^2 + (1/2)*A(x)*(A(x)/(1-A(x)))^2 + A(x)^2/(1-A(x)). - _Noah A Rosenberg_, Jul 22 2026
%e A328122 For n=3 leaves, there are 3 rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with three leaves and no galls: ((A,B),C), ((A,C),B), and ((B,C),A). There are 9 rooted binary leaf-labeled galled trees with a 4-node root gall from which three leaves are descended: 3 with 1 subtree on one side of the root gall and 1 on the other side of the root gall, and 6 with 2 subtrees on one side of the root gall and 0 on the other. There are 6 rooted binary leaf-labeled galled trees with a 3-node root gall from which a leaf and a cherry are descended (3 choices for the leaf times 2 choices for the parental relationship in the root gall). There are 6 rooted binary leaf-labeled galled trees for which a leaf and a 3-node gall descend from the root. There are 12 rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with a 3-node root gall from which a leaf and a 3-node root gall descend. Hence, a(3)=3+9+6+6+12=36.
%e A328122 a(4) = 723 is the number of rooted level-1 phylogenetic networks with 4 labeled leaves.
%p A328122 # see links section
